      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-01-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-01-31T16:33:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Constitutional Amendment - Prohibits outlays for a fiscal year (except those for repayment of debt principal) from exceeding total receipts for that fiscal year (except those derived from borrowing) unless Congress, by a three-fifths rollcall vote of each chamber, authorizes a specific excess of outlays over receipts. </p> <p> <p>Directs the President to submit a balanced budget to Congress annually. <p> <p>Authorizes waivers of these provisions when a declaration of war is in effect or under other specified circumstances involving military conflict. <p>Requires the appropriate congressional committees to report to their respective chambers implementing legislation to achieve a balanced budget without reducing the disbursements of the Federal Old-Age and Survivors Insurance Trust Fund and the Federal Disability Insurance Trust Fund to achieve that goal.<br>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
